# The 3D stack mixes @react-three/fiber@9 + React 19 with @react-three/drei@9
# (whose peer still asks for fiber@8/React 18). The components actually used
# (Float, Stars, Preload) work fine on fiber@9, so we tell npm to tolerate the
# peer mismatch - this is what the local `npm install` did implicitly, and it
# lets the strict `npm ci` in CI (GitHub Actions / Cloudflare) reproduce the
# exact same lockfile tree.
#
# Proper long-term fix: migrate to @react-three/drei@^10 (React 19 native).
legacy-peer-deps=true
